physical_examinations.relevant_findings: On admission: General: Alert and oriented x 3, No acute distress. HEENT: No scleral icterus, mucous membranes moist. Cardiovascular: Regular rate and rhythm, No murmurs, gallops or rubs. Pulmonary: Clear to auscultation bilaterally, No wheezes, rhonchi or rales. Abdomen: Soft, nondistended, focal tenderness with rebound tenderness over right lower quadrant, no guarding, No Rovsing sign. Extremities: No edema, warm and well perfused.
